    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="529"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d529">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/2743</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Norwegian Minister</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BHH1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bryn</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-08-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1916</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Minister</hi>: Please accept my most sincere
                    apologies for the delay in answering your letter of July 22.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d529fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_415">p. 415</ref>.</note>
                    Through some very stupid mistake, it was sent to the wrong bureau and did not
                    reach me until to-day. I took the matter of the delay up at once and I feel sure
                    it will not occur again.</p>
                <pb facs="0713" n="427" xml:id="pg_427"/>
                <p>The information that you sought was in regard to the black list, and you probably
                    have now learned from the newspapers all the details you need. However, I
                    enclose for your information a copy of the note sent to Great Britain. I will
                    give instructions that you are to be kept informed regarding any further action
                    taken by us in this connection.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Frank L. Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
